<html><head><title>Guild Recruitment Festival Begins</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Guild Recruitment Festival Begins</h3><p>This weekend there will be in-game festivities for the Guild Recruitment Festival on all servers, specifically, meeting places in Qeynos and Freeport where you can meet with prospective guilds and guild members.  So get ready to hook up!<br><br>For those who reside in Kelethin or Gorowyn, you are going to need to travel over to Freeport or Qeynos ...guild folks, maybe offer escorts to the lower levels who might not be able to make it?<br><br>EQ2Players posts:<br><br>"The Living Legacy summer events are just kicking off, and now that you’re back, we want make it easy for you to enjoy the rest of the summer celebration by linking back up with old friends or by helping you make some new ones. To help provide you with guidance, we have organized a <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/eq2/posts/list.m?topic_id=421743">Guild Recruitment Fair.</a> We have called upon all the EQII legends that are “living the legacy” by running guilds to gather around and recruit new blood. <br><br>This is a perfect opportunity for you to meet in-game and learn more about the guilds on your server. EQII has a highly developed guild tool system to help you find the right guild and a massive guild community base for you to continue your adventures in a group environment. With guild halls quickly approaching, and several new raid and group zones being released this summer, you’ll need all the help you can get.<br><br>Event Details<br><br>For PvE servers, visits these locations:<br><br>Antonica - For those of the good alignments, come meet at the Claymore in Antonica to exchange information and get to know your fellow Qeynosian or Kelethinian!<br><br>Commonlands - The Overlord decrees the Crossroads as a suitable meeting location for this year's Guild Faire. Do what's right for Freeport and the allies of the Overlord, and ensure only the strongest of guilds brings honor to Freeport!<br><br>For PvP servers, visit these locations:<br><br>Qeynos - For those of the good alignments, come meet at the Claymore Plaza in North Qeynos to exchange information and get to know your fellow Qeynosian or Kelethinain!<br><br>Freeport - The Overlord decrees Execution Plaza in West Freeport as a suitable meeting location for this year's Guild Faire.  Do what's right for Freeport and the allies of the Overlord, and ensure only the strongest of guilds bring honor to Freeport!  <br> <br>The in-game festivities are scheduled Saturday, June 28 through Sunday, June 29; however, you can get ready for the event by visiting our Guild Listing page (COMING SOON!!) to learn more about the participating guilds."</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Tuesday, 24 Jun, 2008<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=42598">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=42598</a><br>Printed On: Wed Sep 5 21:23:04 PDT 2012<br>©2008 IGN Entertainment</font></span>